The paper deals with visual question answering (VQA) and proposes a new method to improve the visual processing of traditional convolutional networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, since the proposed method involves modulating the CNN with a linguistic input, it also falls under the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques and proposes a new approach to improve the performance of VQA models, which makes it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
